%html(lang="#{@lang || 'en'}" class="#{page_classes.gsub('_', '-').downcase} no-js")
  = partial 'layouts/head'
  %body.layout
    .layout--container
      %header.layout--header
        %a(href="/")
          %img.layout--logo(src="#{asset_url('images/nico-hagenburger-ruby-on-rails-2x.png')}" alt="Nico Hagenburger — #{(@keywords || [] + ['Ruby on Rails', 'Haml', 'Sass', 'HTML5'])[0..6].join(', ')}")
        %nav.layout--navigation<
          = link_to 'Home', '/', class: 'layout--navigation-item'
          = link_to 'Blog', '/BLOG.html', class: 'layout--navigation-item'
          = link_to 'Contact', '/CONTACT.html', class: 'layout--navigation-item'
          = link_to 'Portfolio', '/PORTFOLIO.html', class: 'layout--navigation-item'
        .layout--tagline<
          %strong> Hi, I’m Nico Hagenburger
          %br>
          I enjoy designing
          %br>
          clean, simple websites,
          %br>
          developing living style guides
          %br>
          &amp; increasing usability.
      .layout--content
        - if request.path =~ %r(BLOG/)
          %article.post{ :slug => @slug }
            = yield
            = facebook_like
          = partial 'twitter'
        - else
          = yield
    %footer.layout--footer
      %a#github(href="https://github.com/hagenburger")
        %span Fork me on GitHub!
        %span Get free lemonade!
      %small<
        © Nico Hagenburger/Hagenburger GmbH 2000—#{Time.now.year} · Blog posts published under CC share alike licence (except design and artwork or otherwise mentioned)
    = javascript_include_tag 'hagenburger'
  /
    You’ve just read it till the end.
    If you're that fascinated, you definitely have to hire me.
